抱歉，似乎發生一些問題。



Trending Now





 

解答














最佳解答: 
             翻譯完只有一個感覺 
"哲學"還真是"哲學"阿 

(priori - 拉丁文  邏輯猜測的（不是有事實根據的）) 



It is we therefore who carry into the phenomena which we call nature, order and regularity, nay,  
因此是我們造成了所謂的自然有調理及規則性的現象,  
we should never find them in nature, if we ourselves, or the nature of our mind, had not originally placed them there.  
如果我們本身在性格或心態上就從未意識到這個現象, 自然而然地我們就很難去發現它 
For the unity of nature is meant to be a necessary and a priori certain unity in the connection of all phenomena.  
本質的一致性對其相關的所有現象是必須且是邏輯推測下的基礎 
And how should we a priori have arrived at such a synthetical unity,  
我們的邏輯推測是怎樣達到這樣綜合性的一致, 
if the subjective grounds of such unity were not contained a priori in the original sources of our knowledge,  
如果主觀上的一致性並不是來自於我們原本知識下所邏輯推測的結果呢? 

and if those subjective conditions did not at the same time possess objective validity, as being the grounds on which alone an object becomes possible in our experience?… 
如果這些主觀條件並不同時擁有, 以我們所經驗過的對象為基礎的客觀正當性呢? 




 參考資料： 
 靠自己一句一字翻的 


